article.headline: SE Missouri 81, Jacksonville St. 80
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- Will Bogan's follow-up shot with 1.9 seconds left gave Southeast Missouri an 81-80 win Thursday night over Jacksonville State. Bogan grabbed the rebound after Jaycen Herring's shot in the paint was blocked by Erik Adams for Southeast Missouri (8-4, 4-0 Ohio Valley Conference). Jacksonville State (2-9, 0-4) couldn't get a shot off at the end as defender Brandon Foust tipped the inbounds pass to start the clock. Nick Murphy's layup with 12 seconds to play had given the Gamecocks an 80-79 lead. Bogan led Southeast Missouri with 17 points on 7-of-9 shooting. Herring added 14, Marcus Rhodes 13 and Calvin Williams 10. J.J. Wesley tied a school record with eight 3-pointers and scored 28 points for Jacksonville State. DeAndre Bray had 10 points, five steals and a school record-tying 13 assists. Murphy had 14 points and Adams 10 for the Gamecocks, who had trailed by 20 points midway through the first half. They turned that into an 8-point lead with 14 minutes left in the game.
